IMPORTANT NOTE
==============

It's the CVS version of penggy.

It may not compile or freeze your computer.

You need autoconf and automake.

HOW TO BUILD CVS
================

You need automake >= 1.6 and autoconf > 2.53.

penfork/$ autoreconf -fiv
penfork/$ ./configure && make

COMMON TROUBLES
===============

$ automake --version
==> Must answer >= 1.6

$ autoconf --version
==> Must answer >= 2.53

With some distributions, you need to set WANT_AUTOMAKE_1_6=1 before 
launching autoreconf : 

$ WANT_AUTOMAKE_1_6=1 autoreconf -vfi
